% --- SLIDE 1: Project Objectives ---
\section{Project Introduction}
\begin{frame}{Simulation Goals}
    The objective was to create a 3D environment that accurately predicts the motion of a bungee jumper using a discrete-time simulation.
    
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{System Variables:} Tracking position, velocity, and acceleration.
        \item \textbf{Safety Analysis:} Calculating maximum cord stretch and G-forces.
        \item \textbf{Environmental Factors:} Including air resistance (damping) and gravitational pull.
    \end{itemize}
    
    \begin{block}{The Scientific Approach}
        Instead of using one-size-fits-all formulas, we programmed the computer to recalculate the "state" of the jumper every 0.01 seconds.
    \end{block}
\end{frame}

% --- SLIDE 2: Physics Constants & Setup ---
\section{System Configuration}
\begin{frame}{Physical Constants}
    Our Python script utilizes specific constants to ensure the simulation is grounded in real-world physics:

