% --- SLIDE 5: Conclusion ---
\section{Conclusion}
\begin{frame}{Summary and Findings}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Model Reliability:} The use of a small time step ($dt=0.01$) ensures the energy conservation of the system is maintained.
        \item \textbf{Damping Importance:} Without the air resistance ($b=1.8$), the jumper would bounce indefinitely; our model shows a realistic decay in oscillation.
        \item \textbf{Future Improvements:} Adding wind vectors or varying cord elasticity for different jumper weights.
    \end{itemize}

